  "name": {
    "en": "Valerian",
    "zh-Hant": "纈草",
    "zh-Hans": "缬草"
  },
  "scientificName": "Valeriana officinalis",
  "family": "Caprifoliaceae",
  "genus": "Valeriana",
  "description": {
    "en": "Valerian is a perennial flowering plant native to Europe and Asia. The root is used medicinally for its calming and sedative properties.",
    "zh-Hant": "纈草是一種多年生開花植物，原生於歐洲和亞洲。其根部因具有鎮靜和安神特性而被用於藥用。",
    "zh-Hans": "缬草是一种多年生开花植物，原生於欧洲和亚洲。其根部因具有镇静和安神特性而被用于药用。"
  },
  "commonName": {
    "en": "Valerian Root",
    "zh-Hant": "纈草根",
    "zh-Hans": "缬草根"
  },
  "botanicalDescription": {
    "en": "Perennial herb growing to 1-2 meters tall. Leaves are pinnate, divided into several leaflets. Flowers are pink or white, produced in dense clusters. The root has a strong, distinctive odor.",
    "zh-Hant": "多年生草本植物，高1-2米。葉為羽狀，分成多個小葉。花粉紅色或白色，密集成簇生長。根部有強烈的特殊氣味。",
    "zh-Hans": "多年生草本植物，高1-2米。叶为羽状，分成多个小叶。花粉红色或白色，密集成簇生长。根部有强烈的特殊气味。"
  },
